article_title: State-Run Obamacare Exchanges Careening Toward Disaster

article_metadata.author: Sally Pipes

og.description: Obamacare's state-based insurance exchanges were supposed to be self-sufficient this year. But it hasn't worked out that way. Even after $5 billion in federal grants, most are struggling financially.
